4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS FOR STATE AGENCIES PROVIDING
5 INFORMATION TO LEGISLATORS; ALLOWING LEGISLATORS TO SUBMIT A COMPLAINT TO A
6 COMMITTEE WHEN A STATE AGENCY HAS NOT PRODUCED REQUESTED INFORMATION WITHIN 5
7 LEGISLATIVE DAYS OF A WRITTEN REQUEST; PROVIDING FOR A HEARING BY A COMMITTEE;
8 PROVIDING FOR THE COMMITTEE TO VOTE TO REDUCE A STATE AGENCY BUDGET BY NO MORE
9 THAN 5%; PROVIDING THAT INFORMATION FROM THE HEARING BE PRESENTED TO CERTAIN
10 ELECTED OFFICIALS; PROVIDING A DEFINITION; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Legislator request for information from state agency -- complaint
15 process. (1) If a legislator makes a written request for information from a state agency during the regular
16 legislative session, the state agency shall respond with the requested information within 5 legislative days of
17 receiving the legislator's written request. The legislator's written request must be provided to the director of the
18 agency on the same day the request is made to that agency's staff.
19 (2) After the deadline for responding has passed, the legislator may submit a written complaint with
20 the committee that has the general appropriations act in its possession. The complaint must contain the
21 following information:
22 (a) the name of the legislator;
23 (b) the state agency from which information was requested;
24 (c) a copy of the written request for information;
25 (d) a copy of the director's response to the written request, if any; and
26 (e) the legislator's proposed reduction to that agency's budget.
27 (3) The committee in possession of the general appropriations act shall schedule a hearing on the
28 complaint within 3 legislative days of receiving the complaint.
