1 (a) Notice of the time and place of the hearing must be provided to the legislator and the director of
2 the agency within 48 hours of the hearing.
3 (b) The hearing may be postponed by the presiding officer of the committee if either the legislator
4 or the director of the agency is unavailable to attend in person or cannot attend remotely by electronic means
5 due to hospitalization or catastrophic event. The hearing must be rescheduled by the presiding officer of the
6 committee at the earliest date when both the legislator and the director of the agency are available to attend the
7 hearing.
8 (c) The hearing, discussion of the committee, and vote of the committee must be recorded.
9 (4) After the hearing, the committee may vote to reduce the agency's budget by no more than 5%
10 for failing to provide the requested information.
11 (5) The recording of the hearing, discussion of the committee, and vote of the committee must be
12 provided by the committee clerk to the president of the senate, the speaker of the house, and the governor
13 within 10 days of the committee's vote.
14 (6) The governor may determine to include the committee's vote in the director's personnel record
15 and may subject the director to disciplinary measures, including termination.
16 (7) For the purposes of this section:
17 (a) "State agency" means a department, board, quasi-judicial board, commission, committee,
18 authority, council, division, bureau, section, office or any other entity or instrumentality of the executive branch
19 of state government, or any unit of state government over which there is legislative oversight.
20 (b) Written communication includes electronic communication.
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
23 integral part of Title 5, chapter 5, part 1, and the provisions of Title 5, chapter 5, part 1, apply to [section 1].
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
